definitions: Given an unofficial name or nickname to someone or something.
Replaced the original spoken dialogue of a film or video with a translation in another language.
Added a new soundtrack or sound effects to a film, video, or other recording.
Made a copy of an audio or video recording.
Conferred a title or knighthood upon someone.
examples: He was dubbed 'the King of Pop'.
The foreign film was dubbed into English.
New music was dubbed over the original footage.
She dubbed the cassette for her friend.
The queen dubbed him a knight.
